<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-759-013  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 759 013.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Week  July 17 1989 n228 p16(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Calling all specialists: telecom expertise commands highersalaries, poll shows. (Communications)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sabatini, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Telecommunications specialists registered impressive salaryincreases averaging 11.8 percent in a survey of the overallManagement Information Systems (MIS) job market compared to sevenm percent for telecom executives.andP;  The 1988 Salary Survey of DataProcessing Professional Positions indicated strong demand for:operations technicians, with an average salary of $26,900; networkdesigners, with an average salary of $28,800; and softwareanalysts, with an average of $35,300.andP;  Salaries of MIS specialistssuch as senior software programmers and computer operatorsaveraged $48,800 and $29,000, respectively.andP;  Corporate trends suchas data center relocation have placed emphasis on the specificskills involved in network support functions, and some companiesare having trouble keeping employees who have been trained in aspecific area, leading to programs involving bonuses, specialprojects, promotions and raises.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     MISTelecommunicationsPersonnelSalaryCompaniesSurvey.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>